revision.text:
{{advert|date=August 2011}}
The '''Azerbaijan Voluntary Military Patriotism Technical Sport Society''', or '''VMPTSTS''' for short, are [[military]] institutes established in major cities in [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news |url= http://en.trend.az/news/azerbaijan/1513443.html|title= Azerbaijani President awards employees of voluntary military-patriotic sports-technical society with Tereggi medal|date=July 28, 2009|publisher="[[Trend News Agency]]" |accessdate=July 28, 2009}}</ref> The institutes teach essential combat techniques, including how to be sniper and a parachutist.
==Sniper course== The school offers a 45-day-long course that teaches [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijanis]] over the age of 15 essential combat techniques, including how to be snipers. It is Azerbaijan’s only non-profit school for snipers and the only organization outside of the [[Azerbaijani Armed Forces|military]] that provides such training.<ref name="EurasiaNet">{{cite news |url= http://www.eurasianet.org/node/63468|title=Azerbaijan: Teaching the ABCs of How to Be a Sniper|date=March 11, 2011|publisher=EurasiaNet|accessdate=March 11, 2011}}</ref> Participants (divided equally between males and females) are drilled in both the theory and practice of sniper shooting. Aside from [[first aid]] and how to load and fire, students dig into such topics as “The Basics of [[Hand-to-Hand Combat]],” military topography, intelligence gathering and international laws on the use of [[sniper rifle]]s.<ref name="News.Az">{{cite news |url= http://www.news.az/articles/society/33811|title=Azerbaijani snipers 'never fire' at civilians|date=April 5, 2011|publisher=News.Az|accessdate=April 5, 2011}}</ref><ref name="EurasiaNetApril">{{cite news |url= http://www.eurasianet.org/node/63241|title=Azerbaijan's Young Amateur Snipers |date=April 6, 2011|publisher=EurasiaNet|accessdate=April 6, 2011}}</ref>
According to Walid Gardashov, which is organizing the lessons, the school serves to "develop feelings of bravery and courage in young people, which will turn a teenager into a bold, fearless soldier in the future."<ref name="Hürriyet Daily News and Economic Review">{{cite news |url= http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/n.php?n=azerbaijan-launches-sniper-lessons-for-youth-2011-04-07|title=Azerbaijan launches sniper lessons for youth|date=April 7, 2011|publisher="[[Hürriyet Daily News and Economic Review]]"|accessdate=April 7, 2011}}</ref> The courses is free public school students, while older participants pay 50 [[Azerbaijani manat|manats]] ($63) for the course.<ref name="EurasiaNet"/>
==Weapons== Some of the weapons used during the training include:<ref name="EurasiaNet"/> *[[Dragunov sniper rifle|Dragunov SVD]] *[[Tavor TAR-21]] *[[Heckler & Koch MP5]] *[[Istiglal Anti-Material Rifle|Istiglal IST-14.5 Anti-Material Rifle]]
