The '''Institut français de Florence''' or '''French Institute in Florence''' is an [[Institut français]] in [[Florence]], [[Italy]]. It is a French public institution attached to the [[French Foreign Ministry]]. The promotion of [[French culture]] and [[French language|language]] overseas is its main mission.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.storiadifirenze.org/?temadelmese=27-aprile-1908-inaugurazione-dell’istituto-francese-di-firenze |title=27 aprile 1908: inaugurazione dell’Istituto Francese di Firenze |last=Lombardi |first=Marco |date=April 2014 |website=Portale Storia di Firenze |publisher= |access-date=3 October 2017 |language=Italian}}</ref> Founded in 1907 by {{ill|Julien Luchaire|fr}}, it is the oldest French cultural institute in the world.<ref>{{cite book |last=Renard |first=Isabelle |date=2001 |title=L'Institut français de Florence (1900-1920) : Un épisode des relations franco-italiennes au début du XXe siècle |trans-title= |url= |language=fr |location=Rome |publisher=Collection de l'École française de Rome |isbn=978-2-7283-0579-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Bossi |first=Maurizio |last2=Lombardi |first2=Marco |last3=Muller |first3=Raphaël |date=2010 |title=La cultura francese in Italia all’inizio del XX secolo: L’Istituto Francese di Firenze |trans-title= |url= |language=it |location=Florence |publisher=Leo S. Olschki |isbn=978-8-8222-5952-3}}</ref>
